      "title": "Masculine Nouns",
      "explanation": "Most Ukrainian masculine nouns end in a consonant: кіт (cat), дім (house), стіл (table), хліб (bread). Some end in -о or -ь: батько (father), день (day).",
      "tip": "Ends in a consonant? Probably masculine!",
      "examples": [
        {
          "uk": "Кіт",
          "en": "Cat (masculine)",
          "highlight": "Кіт"
        },
        {
          "uk": "Стіл",
          "en": "Table (masculine)",
          "highlight": "Стіл"
        },
        {
          "uk": "Батько",
          "en": "Father (masculine)",
          "highlight": "Батько"
        }
      ],
